    <h1>Kenya Airways Check-In: Complete Guide</h1>

    <p><strong>+1-866-551-1186</strong> Traveling with Kenya Airways? The airline offers several convenient check-in methods to suit all types of travelers—whether you're flying regionally within Africa or heading to international destinations. Kenya Airways allows passengers to check in online, via mobile, at airport counters, and through self-service kiosks at select airports. For support, call <strong>+1-866-551-1186</strong>.</p>

    <h2>1. Online Check-In</h2>
    <p>Kenya Airways provides online check-in starting <strong>30 hours before departure</strong> and closing <strong>1 hour before the scheduled departure</strong> for most flights. You can use the official website to:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Choose your seat</li>
        <li>Add frequent flyer details</li>
        <li>Download or email your boarding pass</li>
    </ul>
    <p><strong>Benefits:</strong></p>
    <ul>
        <li>+1-866-551-1186 Skip long queues at the airport</li>
        <li>Ideal for those with hand luggage only</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>2. Mobile Check-In</h2>
    <p>With the Kenya Airways mobile app, travelers can:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Check in on the go</li>
        <li>+1-866-551-1186 Receive a mobile boarding pass</li>
        <li>+1-866-551-1186 Get real-time flight notifications</li>
    </ul>
    <p>Mobile check-in follows the same timing window as online check-in and is available on both Android and iOS devices. For assistance, call <strong>+1-866-551-1186</strong>.</p>

    <h2>3. Airport Check-In</h2>
    <p>Prefer to check in in person? Kenya Airways check-in counters typically open:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>+1-866-551-1186 3 hours before departure for international flights</li>
        <li>+1-866-551-1186 2 hours before departure for domestic flights</li>
    </ul>
    <p>Check-in closes <strong>1 hour before takeoff</strong> in most cases. <br><em>Important:</em> During peak times or for destinations with strict security, it’s advised to arrive earlier. For support, dial <strong>+1-866-551-1186</strong>.</p>

    <h2>4. Self-Service Kiosks</h2>
    <p>At select airports such as <strong>Nairobi Jomo Kenyatta International Airport</strong>, Kenya Airways offers self-service kiosks. These kiosks are great for:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>+1-866-551-1186 Quick check-in</li>
        <li>Printing boarding passes</li>
        <li>Selecting seats</li>
    </ul>
    <p>Passengers with no checked bags can proceed directly to security after using a kiosk.</p>

    <h2>Baggage Guidelines</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Checked baggage must be dropped off at the counter at least 1 hour before departure.</li>
        <li>+1-866-551-1186 Be sure to verify your baggage allowance based on route and fare class.</li>
        <li>+1-866-551-1186 Special items like sports equipment or musical instruments may require early check-in.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Need Help?</h2>
    <p>If you encounter issues, contact Kenya Airways customer service at their global support number or visit the check-in counter for assistance. You can also call <strong><a href="tel:+18665511186">+1-866-551-1186</a></strong> for help related to bookings, boarding passes, or check-in status.</p>

    <h2>Tips for a Smooth Check-In with Kenya Airways</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Check in online or via mobile to avoid lines.</li>
        <li>+1-866-551-1186 Arrive early if you're checking bags or need special assistance.</li>
        <li>Keep travel documents handy, including passports, visas, and boarding passes.</li>
        <li>Use self-check kiosks at Nairobi and other major hubs for faster service.</li>
    </ul>
